# Clerk Authentication Rules

## Positive Directives

- Use `clerkMiddleware()` with `createRouteMatcher()` to protect routes
- Sync Clerk users to the database via the `/api/webhooks/clerk` webhook (handle user.created, user.updated, user.deleted)
- Always verify webhook signatures using the `svix` library
- Use `auth()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server` in Server Components and Server Actions to get the current user
- Differentiate ATTENDEE vs ORGANIZER roles using the `Role` enum in the database
- Use Clerk's `<SignInButton>`, `<SignedIn>`, `<SignedOut>`, and `<UserButton>` components for auth UI

## Negative Rules

- NEVER check authentication in client components - always delegate to middleware or server-side checks
- NEVER store Clerk user data as the sole source of truth - always sync to the database User model
- NEVER bypass the webhook signature verification

## Verification Steps

- Confirm middleware protects `/organizer` and `/attendee` routes
- Test the Clerk webhook by creating a test user and verifying the database record is created
- Confirm `auth()` calls correctly reject unauthenticated access in Server Actions
